1. <img> tag: for displaying images

<img src="image.jpg" alt="A scenic mountain view" width="400" height="300">


2. <figure> and <figcaption> tag : for images with caption

<figure>
  <img src="sunset.jpg" alt="Sunset at the beach" width="500">
  <figcaption> A beautiful beach sunset </figcaption>
</figure>


3. <audio> tag: for embedding sound
'controls'- show the audio player with controls so the user can play sound

<audio controls>                                             // audio player
  <source src="music.mp3" type="audio/mpeg">                 // audio file and format
  Your browser does not support the audio element.           // message if audio not play 
</audio>


4. <video> tag: for embedding video
width='600': sets the width of the video to 600 pixels.

<video controls width="600">                                //Create a video player that is 600px wide and has built-in controls.
  <source src="movie.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  Your browser does not support the video tag.
</video>


5. <iframe> tag: for embedding external content

- FOR YT VIDEOS
<iframe width="560" height="315"                          //sets size of video
  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID"
  title="YouTube video"                                   // video title for accessibility 
  frameborder="0"                                         // no border around the video
  allowfullscreen>                                        //  allow full screen mode
</iframe>

- FOR PDF FILE
<iframe src="file.pdf" width="600" height="500">
  This browser does not support PDFs. Please download the file.
</iframe>



